# gen170 (dynamic knowledge): the testable "need external research" signal. Asked
# to define a topic it does not know, parrot0 does not pretend and does not just
# wall — it HONESTLY flags the gap, says it would document itself from static
# Wikipedia, and RECORDS the topic. The brain does no network (the "no network"
# rule forbids outsourcing intelligence, not reading static knowledge); the actual
# fetch is the external scripts/learn.py. "what do you need to research?" is the
# testable readout. Fresh held-out topics, so nothing is memorized.
> tell me about quaternions
< I don't actually know about quaternions yet — I won't pretend. I've flagged it to document myself from Wikipedia; once my learner fetches it, I'll know it next time.
> what is a perfect number?
< I don't actually know about perfect number yet — I won't pretend. I've flagged it to document myself from Wikipedia; once my learner fetches it, I'll know it next time.
